definition: to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)
to be born/to give birth/life/to grow/raw/uncooked/student
-ly/structural particle: used before a verb or adjective, linking it to preceding modifying adverbial adjunct

sentences.english: You are not using consecutive start position numbers.
sentences.chinese: 你必须使用连续的出生地点序号。

sentences.english: Please attach a copy of verified document for place of birth and latest school report.
sentences.chinese: 请附出生地点证明文件及最近成绩表副本。

sentences.english: Document give details of a person's date and place of birth.
sentences.chinese: 载有某人出生日和出生地细情的文件。

sentences.english: My father loved to build up Montaigne, where he was born.
sentences.chinese: 我先父热心于建设他的出生地蒙田。

sentences.english: You have to use all consecutive position.
sentences.chinese: 你必须使用连续的出生地点序号。

sentences.english: Other experts believe Kahn was also influenced by the part of Philadelphia where he grew up.
sentences.chinese: 其它专家认为康也受到其出生地费城的影响。

sentences.english: At 18, Besson returned to his birthplace of Paris.
sentences.chinese: 18岁的时候，贝松回到他的出生地巴黎。

sentences.english: Even the land of Obama'sbirth snubs him?
sentences.chinese: 即使奥巴马的出生地都冷落他么？

sentences.english: He has a sentimental attachment to his birth-place.
sentences.chinese: 他对自己的出生地有眷恋之情。

sentences.english: That is the place where the famous poet was born.
sentences.chinese: 那就是这位著名诗人的出生地。

sentences.english: Both tower-like nebulas are cocoons of young stars.
sentences.chinese: 鹰状星云是著名的恒星出生地。

sentences.english: People ask me what my nationality is, I say Texan.
sentences.chinese: 别人问我的出生地，我会说我是德克萨斯人。

sentences.english: The primary source of his identity is who he is—his father and his birthplace.
sentences.chinese: 帕普的身份的主体是他的父亲和他的出生地。

sentences.english: It's from Pingtung County in the south, where she was born.
sentences.chinese: 那块鲔鱼来自南方的屏东，她的出生地。

sentences.english: The old photo () () () () him to find his birthplace.
sentences.chinese: 这张老照片使他寻找自己的出生地成为可能。

definition: to migrate/to move to a new place of residence
to settle (in some city, country etc)/to take up residence
to move (from one residence to another)
